Text: Our second studio project comprises of working with Kevin Payne, a now-courier man that was a Greyhound race commentator ten years ago! We had our first client meeting with him last week and it went swimmingly.
He is a very passionate man with a clear vision.
This was nice to observe and experience because it essentially narrowed the projects pathway for the team and I. .
In terms of team dynamics, we are a team of four women.
At the moment things are good because there are always open discussions for new ideas.
It'll be interesting to see how our team dynamics unfold over the course of the length of the project.
In comparison to the last project - personalities as a whole differ - although Yoko and I were in the same team in the last project, which is the only similarity.
I have been conducting my own research in terms of the project.

Before the client meeting I thought the core principle of this project was to produce some machine learning model for Kevin, so I have been hastily loaning 'machine learning' books, jut to clue up on what is to come.
But it seems as though our client is happy with data automation into a large database.
His main problem is having to copy and paste data into an excel spreadsheet.
He mentioned that the last group of people had no luck in scraping data off the TAB website and Teacher1 found that too using Excel - so this is an aspect I will delve to solve.
Anyhow, I suppose that is my current thoughts on the project thus far.
Just excited to plan with the team and produce a proposal! :)
